column1: Accumulation Rate Records for Low Precipitation Scenario Assimilated
Time is in years before 1950 CE (BP).
Accumulation rate is dimensionless (fraction relative to the reference period).
Values are for the middle of the interval. For example the value at time 100 BP is the average over time 75 to 125 BP.
The timescales are all equivalent to the GICC05 timescale.

For GISP2 cite: Cuffey K. M. and Clow G. D.: Temperature accumulation and ice sheet elevation in central Greenland through the last deglacial transition. Journal of Geophysical Research: Oceans. 102. 26 383-26 396. 1997.

For NEEM cite: Rasmussen S. O. and Abbott P. and Blunier T. and Bourne A. and Brook E. J. and Buchardt S. L. and Buizert C. and Chappellaz J. and Clausen H. B. and Cook E. et al.: A First chronology for the North Greenland Eemian Ice Drilling (NEEM) ice core. Climate of the Past. 9. 2013.

For GRIP and NGRIP and Dye3 cite: Badgeley J. A. and Steig E. J. and Hakim G. J. and Fudge T. J.: Greenland temperature and precipitation over the last 20000 years using data assimilation. Climate of the Past. in press. 2020. (preprint: https://doi.org/10.5194/cp-2019-164)
